---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/layout/Section.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Content Styleguide (Dev) | CoClaw"
  description="Visual baseline for Markdown content styles."
  robots="noindex, nofollow"
>
  <div class="bg-background min-h-screen overflow-x-hidden relative">
    <Section containerClass="max-w-4xl mx-auto pt-24 pb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Content Styleguide</h1>
      <p class="text-default-700 dark:text-default-500">
        This page is a visual regression baseline for Markdown/MDX-rendered content.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section containerClass="max-w-4xl mx-auto pb-24">
      <article class="c-content prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2>Typography</h2>
        <p>
          Regular paragraph text with an <a href="#">inline link</a>, some <code>inline code</code>,
          and a keyboard hint <kbd>Cmd</kbd> + <kbd>K</kbd>. Here is a <mark>highlight</mark>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Another paragraph to show spacing and rhythm. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur
          adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua.
        </p>

        <h3>Blockquote</h3>
        <blockquote>
          <p>
            “If content doesn’t look good by default, authors will fight the system with ad-hoc
            classes everywhere.”
          </p>
          <p><strong>Goal:</strong> one container class; everything else is automatic.</p>
        </blockquote>

        <hr />

        <h2>Lists</h2>
        <h3>Unordered</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>First item</li>
          <li>
            Second item with nested list
            <ul>
              <li>Nested A</li>
              <li>Nested B</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Third item</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Ordered</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Step one</li>
          <li>Step two</li>
          <li>
            Step three with nested steps
            <ol>
              <li>Sub-step 3.1</li>
              <li>Sub-step 3.2</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Code</h2>
        <pre><code class="language-bash">pnpm dev
pnpm build</code></pre>

        <h2>Table</h2>
        <p>Tables should be readable, theme-safe, and horizontally scrollable on small screens.</p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Component</th>
              <th>What It Does</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>.c-content</code></td>
              <td>Scopes default content styles to Markdown output.</td>
              <td>Prevents global tag styling from leaking into marketing UI.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>table</code></td>
              <td>Provides spacing, borders, zebra rows, and hover.</td>
              <td>Also supports overflow scrolling on mobile.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>VeryLongHeaderValueToTestOverflow</td>
              <td>Ensures layout is resilient when content gets wide.</td>
              <td>Scroll horizontally rather than breaking layout.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>Details</h2>
        <details>
          <summary>Expandable section</summary>
          <p>
            Use <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> in Markdown for optional advanced notes without extra components.
          </p>
        </details>

        <h2>Definition List</h2>
        <dl>
          <dt>Token</dt>
          <dd>A semantic design variable that stays stable across light/dark themes.</dd>
          <dt>Drift</dt>
          <dd>When ad-hoc styles accumulate and pages slowly become inconsistent.</dd>
        </dl>
      </article>
    </Section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
